SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYMonday 11 April S10 V2 Huddersfield host Luton in a key game for both promotion-chasing clubs as they eye a spot in the Premier League next season. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Malmo FF vs IF Elfsborg: Champions Malmo play the second match of the new Sweden season. They won their opener but Elfsborg suffered a surprise home defeat last weekend.M2 IFK Varnamo vs IK Sirius: Sirius have never lost to Varnamo with five wins and one draw in six past clashes.M3 Vejle BK vs Viborg FF: Viborg were 2-0 home winners when they last hosted Vejle one month ago. Now they meet again in the post-season playoffs in Denmark.M4 Antalyaspor vs Hatayspor: Antalyaspor are on a winning streak of four successive games. Hatayspor have three draws and two victories from their past five clashes.M5 Maccabi Tel Aviv vs Maccabi Haifa: Third placed Maccabi Tel Aviv are 10 points behind leaders Maccabi Haifa in the Israeli league standings.M6 Brescia vs Parma: Brescia have drawn four of their five fixtures. Parma have gone nine matches without a loss.M7 Bologna vs Sampdoria: Bologna have not won in their past five games but did take a point off leaders Milan on Monday. Sampdoria have lost four of their previous five outings.M8 Huddersfield Town vs Luton Town: Huddersfield are third in the Championship, one point above fourth placed Luton, who had to play in midweek and drew at lowly Peterborough.M9 Paris FC vs Dijon: Paris are third and just two points off an automatic promotion places. Dijon are mid-table in the French second division but gone five games without losing.M10 Rayo Vallecano vs Valencia: Rayo are on a run of 10 games without a win. Valencia have gone six matches without defeat. Suggested permutation: R4.00 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1,2